Activities marking the end of the 2020 Armed Forces remembrance day have been rounded off across the country with a wreath laying ceremony by President Muhammadu Buhari and his vice, Professor Yemi Osinbajo together with the nation's security chiefs, Governors in various states and other important dignitaries.  In the nationâ€™s capital, President Buhari, Services Chiefs, the leadership of the National Assembly, judiciary and members of the diplomatic corps paid their respects to the heroes at the Remembrance Arcade in Abuja. The Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF), Mr Boss Mustapha and the Minister of Information, Culture and Tourism, Alhaji Lai Mohammed spoke on the significance of the day. One of the widows of the late soldiers, Mrs Gift Aloko also spoke about their travails since the death of her loved one.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that January 15 is set aside annually to honour members of the military serving and the fallen heroes who laid down their lives during the first and second world Wars, Nigerian civil wars, international support missions, and various security operations, particularly the current war against terrorism. 